Source: pg-datasentinel
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/datasentinel/pg_datasentinel

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-datasentinel
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-datasentinel
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Observability and activity monitoring extension for PostgreSQL
  pg_datasentinel adds observability views for backend memory usage, temporary
  file usage, checkpoint activity, vacuum and analyze events, and XID/MXID
  wraparound risk estimation.
  The module must be loaded via shared_preload_libraries because it allocates
  shared memory and hooks into PostgreSQL activity logging.
